      "html_url": "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/fae9623c8db703f8277755b606420400a6cb0d3c",
      "tree": {
        "sha": "47983c026efb526b3ed2b04a4b25fae0b80c456b",
        "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/trees/47983c026efb526b3ed2b04a4b25fae0b80c456b"
      },
      "verification": {
        "verified": false,
        "reason": "no_user",
        "payload": "tree 47983c026efb526b3ed2b04a4b25fae0b80c456b\nparent bcbf5bae1645605939f0700c438f0cafb47056dc\nauthor MarcoFalke <*~=`'#}+{/-|&$^_@721217.xyz> 1781024876 +0200\ncommitter MarcoFalke <*~=`'#}+{/-|&$^_@721217.xyz> 1781028072 +0200\n\ntest: Add FakeNodeClock m_clock to TestChain100Setup\n\nCurrently, all test cases using TestChain100Setup or a derived class\nlike BuildChainTestingSetup are using mocktime by default due to the\nSetMockTime call in the TestChain100Setup ctor.\n\nThis is confusing, because test cases using mocktime explicitly seem to\nimply that before they set the mocktime, real time was used.\n\nE.g. index_reorg_crash claimed in a comment to \"Enable mock time\".\n\nFix this issue by adding a FakeNodeClock m_clock field to\nTestChain100Setup. Then, use the m_clock instead of explicit calls to\nSetMockTime or to a (now) shadowing local FakeNodeClock variable.\n",
        "signature": "-----BEGIN SSH SIGNATURE-----\nU1NIU0lHAAAAAQAAADMAAAALc3NoLWVkMjU1MTkAAAAgqxY/aMPiuXoCFn6iAEyAhvUqFX\njanTudd31Jtt35ct0AAAADZ2l0AAAAAAAAAAZzaGE1MTIAAABTAAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5\nAAAAQNH8LwS+T+7GH0JHxJsBPcralo/Hl4Y0DfRgZfaEgYM2SeXAveA03ImLBJtO+a5rGv\nO0zftG5U6jnLu740Cc8ws=\n-----END SSH SIGNATURE-----"
      },
      "parents": [
        {
          "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/commits/bcbf5bae1645605939f0700c438f0cafb47056dc",
          "sha": "bcbf5bae1645605939f0700c438f0cafb47056dc",
          "html_url": "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/bcbf5bae1645605939f0700c438f0cafb47056dc"
        }
      ],
      "message": "test: Add FakeNodeClock m_clock to TestChain100Setup\n\nCurrently, all test cases using TestChain100Setup or a derived class\nlike BuildChainTestingSetup are using mocktime by default due to the\nSetMockTime call in the TestChain100Setup ctor.\n\nThis is confusing, because test cases using mocktime explicitly seem to\nimply that before they set the mocktime, real time was used.\n\nE.g. index_reorg_crash claimed in a comment to \"Enable mock time\".\n\nFix this issue by adding a FakeNodeClock m_clock field to\nTestChain100Setup. Then, use the m_clock instead of explicit calls to\nSetMockTime or to a (now) shadowing local FakeNodeClock variable.",
      "committer": {
        "name": "MarcoFalke",
        "email": "*~=`'#}+{/-|&$^_@721217.xyz",
        "date": "2026-06-09T18:01:12Z"
