        "payload": "tree 5053f94c0855b23ff38d8797470fc8cd5444e2b6\nparent fae9623c8db703f8277755b606420400a6cb0d3c\nauthor MarcoFalke <*~=`'#}+{/-|&$^_@721217.xyz> 1781025919 +0200\ncommitter MarcoFalke <*~=`'#}+{/-|&$^_@721217.xyz> 1781028311 +0200\n\ntest: Use FakeNodeClock in more places\n\nThe context is easier to reason about: E.g.,\n\n* in TestBasicMining it allows to drop manual SetMockTime(0) calls,\n* in connections_desirable_service_flags it allows to drop manual calls\n  to SetMockTime(GetTime<std::chrono::seconds>() + _n_) and replace them\n  by operator+=(_n_)\n* in wallet_tests it clarifies that the mocktime does not persist\n  outside the AddTx function\n",
        "signature": "-----BEGIN SSH SIGNATURE-----\nU1NIU0lHAAAAAQAAADMAAAALc3NoLWVkMjU1MTkAAAAgqxY/aMPiuXoCFn6iAEyAhvUqFX\njanTudd31Jtt35ct0AAAADZ2l0AAAAAAAAAAZzaGE1MTIAAABTAAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5\nAAAAQLzDZhT9paySE+g32KGarmA93jkaiwQzaldywcyv8VMbFpyFueVh2PlQtU6YjXLRuF\nAKq/Lsi1WnM9INbtMP7gQ=\n-----END SSH SIGNATURE-----"
